text: I used to go here when I needed something from HD.   Then I met the owner.  I'm not a hateful person, but this guy got my blood boiling within seconds and is nothing short of a complete asshat.   He's vulgar, unprofessional, and all-around unpleasant. He is made of the same ingredients as his food; lips and assholes.   The dogs are convenient, but this man will never receive another cent from me.

Red Hot Chicago is a nice score for those times when you're heading to Home Depot and don't have time to stop for a decent meal, because your wife is nagging you about getting back to finish some stupid home improvement project.  A dog, chips, and pop will cost you $4. They really ought to serve beer, though.
